APPLY WORK ETHICS, VALUES, & QUALITY PRINCIPLES
-this competency means that the trainer demonstrates and promotes ethical behavior, positive, and quality standards in all training activities.
-it involves being honest, fair, respectful, and responsible, ehilr ensuring that all outputs and performance meet industry and training standards.
-The trainer also models these behaviors so learners can apply them in real work place situations.
Examples
-Fair Assessment Practice
  >The trainer eveluates learners objectively based on set criteria without favoritism
-Honesty and Integrity
  >The trainer emphasizes that learners must perform tasks on their own, and avoid cheating during assessments
-Respect in the Training Environment
  >The trainer treats all learners with respect, regardless background or skill level.
-Quality Work Standards
  >In a technical task (ex. caregiving or housekeeping) the trainer ensures that learners follow standard procedures and procedure quality outputs
-Professional Behavior
  >The trainer models punctuality, proper attire, and good communication.
-Continues Improvement
  >The trainer encourages learners to improve their performance based on feedback.

Importance
-Builds trust and credibility
-ensures high-quality training outcomes
-Develops responsible and professional workers
-Promotes positive workplace culture

Working effectively in Voctional Education and Training (TVET) means trainer can perform their roles efficiently and professionally within the training environment.

Key Apsects:
-Apply CBT principles and training standards
-Manage time, resources, and training activities effective
-Maintain a safe and organized learning environment
-Communicate and collaborate with learners and co-trainers
-Follow institutional and industry policies and prcedures
-Demonstrate professionalism and adaptability
Examples
-Training Session Management
  >The trainer prepares lesson plans, tools, and materials before class and follows a clear schedule
-Applying CBT Approach
  >The trainer allows learners to practice tasks (ex. caregiving skills) until they achieve competency, rather than focusing only on lectures.
-Resource Management
  >The trainer ensures that tools and equipment are avilable and properly used during training.
-Collaboration with Colleagues
  >The trainer coordinates with ther trainers to alin lessons and share best practices
-Maintaining Safety and Order
  >The trainer enforces safety rules in workshops or laboratories
-Industry Linkages
  >The trainer communicates with industry partners for updates on current practices or for on-the-job training opportunities.

Impoertance
-Ensures effective training delivery
-Improves learner performance and competency
-Aligns training with industry standards
-Promotes professionalism and efficiency

